  "prompt": "After finishing urination, when I walk one drop of urine comes out. I don't know why. How do I cure this problem?",
  "response": "I'm not a doctor, but there are a few general suggestions that might help with post-void dribbling, which is what you're describing:\n\n1. **Pelvic Floor Exercises**: Also known as Kegel exercises, these can strengthen muscles around the bladder and urethra, potentially improving control over urination. \n   \n2. **Double Voiding**: After you think you're done urinating, wait a moment and try to urinate again. This can help ensure that the bladder is fully emptied.\n\n3. **Urethral Milking**: Gently applying pressure to the area behind the scrotum and along the urethra can help push out any remaining urine.\n\n4. **Stay Hydrated and Healthy**: Generally taking good care of your overall health and maintaining proper hydration can help avoid issues with urination.\n\n5. **Schedule Regular Check-Ups**: Visiting a healthcare professional regularly to discuss urinary issues can help prevent and address any underlying conditions.\n\nRemember that it's always best to discuss such issues with a healthcare provider for advice tailored to your specific situation and health history.",
